node.text: Australian surf-rock trio @Skegss bring two songs off of their latest album, Rehearsal, to the shoebox in this week's Sidestripe Sessions. Hear "Under the Thunder" and "Bush TV," alongside artwork by @Irvine69.

node.text: Though her career began in classical music, painting, and analog photography, @HelenaGarza_'s field of inspiration is boundless. In this project, she shares a VR painting – a proposal of reality understood from figurative memories and the present environment in constant change and reconstruction. Learn more about her unique explorations in art at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: Take a step into the surreal landscape of Chloé Bernard’s (@chloyeah_suzzies) 3D Mural, created in an abandoned footbridge. Get to know more about the tattooist, graphic designer, skateboarder and painter at vans.com/chloebernard

node.text: Artist, musician, and surfer, Alex Knost (@knostthankyou) has been experimenting in surfing’s subculture for over a decade. Regardless of the medium, he often challenges relationships between texture and color while breaking the regiment of art forms. Watch his film about surfing and the exploration of dissonant sound at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: Instead of making ads that talk about creativity, we recruited our family of creatives to go out and celebrate creativity in its purest form. Drawings, sculptures, videos, digital animations, and things we didn’t even see coming. See how they all came to life at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: @VansVault and @JJJJound come together to reinterpret the Style 37. The short-lived style was only in production for one year before its design evolved into the Sk8-Hi. Sometime in the 1990s, Vans reissued the Vault by Vans Style 37, and since then, it has been rediscovered as the Sk8-Mid VLT LX. The Vault by Vans x JJJJound Sk8-Mid VLT LX is available tomorrow 8/14 at select Vault dealers globally. For more info, visit vans.com/droplist
